BACKGROUND CONTEXT: Various designs of total disc replacement (TDR) devices have 
been compared to anterior cervical discectomy and fusion (ACDF) with favorable 
outcomes in FDA-approved investigational device exemption trials. The design of 
M6-C with a compressible viscoelastic nuclear core and an annular structure is 
substantially different than prior designs and has previously demonstrated 
favorable kinematics and clinical outcomes in small case series.
